RIYADH: The first group of Hajj 2022 pilgrims from Bangladesh arrived in Jeddah on Sunday.   Over 400 Bangladeshi pilgrims were greeted with gifts of Zamzam water, roses, and dates on arrival at King Abdulaziz International Airport in Jeddah. Bangladesh’s ambassador to Saudi Arabia, Dr. Mohammed Javed Patwary, was also present at the airport to welcome Hajj pilgrims from his country.   